(SAY, 1829)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[806,1421,369,727]" pageId="10" pageNumber="707">
<emphasis box="[806,1074,369,390]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="707">Larva and puparium:</emphasis>
Anterior fold with a wide spicule band extending from just above the antennomaxillary organs to the apex. Spicules extending almost to halfway along longitudinal folds of the prothorax, at least to beyond the middle sensillum on mid-dorsal folds. Crochets of metathoracic prolegs forming a w-shaped band. Metathorax with lateral folds bearing broad setae at sensilla 4 and 5. Anal lobe with broad setae. Posterior breathing tube with AP 1.6¥ length of TR, faintly coriacous otherwise shining and not tapering. Pupal spiracles (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 48–53" captionStartId="47.[164,254,1555,1574]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1523]" captionTargetId="figure-0@47.[323,1283,195,1525]" captionTargetPageId="47" captionText="Figures 48–53. Pupal spiracles of Copestylum, scanning electron photomicrographs. 48, 50, Copestylum fornax; 48, dorsolateral view length 0.38 mm; 50, whole view from above scale as indicated; 49, Copestylum satur, lateral view length 0.73 mm; 51, 53, Copestylum marginatum; 51, dorsolateral view length 0.82 mm; 53, sculpture between openings, view from above; 52, Copestylum limbipenne, sculpture between openings, view from above." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443508/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="707">Figs 51, 53</figureCitation>
) about 1.3¥ length of AP.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="707" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[806,1421,765,1031]" pageId="10" pageNumber="707">
<emphasis box="[806,1312,765,786]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="707">
Taxonomic notes: 
<taxonomicName box="[1027,1312,765,786]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="707" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="narginatum">Copestylum narginatum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Williston, 1887" authorityName="Williston" authorityYear="1887" box="[933,1285,795,817]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="707" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbipenne">
<emphasis box="[933,1095,795,817]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="707">C. limbipenne</emphasis>
Williston, 1887
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier, 2009" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="707" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncatum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="707">C. truncatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[861,947,826,847]" pageId="10" pageNumber="707" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Giglio-Tos, 1892" authorityName="Giglio-Tos" authorityYear="1892" box="[1007,1303,826,848]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="707" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simile">
<emphasis box="[1007,1109,826,847]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="707">C. simile</emphasis>
Giglio-Tos, 
<quantity box="[1248,1303,826,847]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.80568" pageId="10" pageNumber="707" unit="in" value="1892.0">1892</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in having the AP the same length as or longer than the width of the TR. It is distinguished from these species by the numerous spicules on the anterior ends of the longitudinal folds of the dorsum of the prothorax, wide band of spicules on the anterior fold, and a nontapering posterior breathing tube.
</paragraph>
